OL,4,C'crawl off train' at London King's
OL,5,CCross
OL,7,F"There are loads of people who can't,
OL,8,Fand it was only the train manager on
OL,9,Fthe 11 o'clock train going north saw
OL,10,Fme getting off the train that somebody
OL,11,Fcame along. If they hadn't have seen
OL,12,Fthat, I don't know whether I would
OL,13,Fhave got off. I would have had to have
OL,14,Fpulled the emergency cord and then
OL,15,Fdelayed the train going north."
OL,17,FShe said she had a call from a senior
OL,18,Fmember of London North Eastern Railway
OL,19,F(LNER) on Monday night and they had
OL,20,Falso been in touch on Tuesday morning
OL,21,Fto say an investigation has started.
